						               													<description>A miniatures game, centered around the Roman Empire.  The rules cover the period between the time when Augustus seized power (25 BC), right through the period of the Empire&amp;rsquo;s height, down through the crisis of the third century, and ending with the reign of Aurelian (275 AD).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Shooting and combat are determined using a number of ten-sided dice.  The number depending on the size of the units involved. The dice rolls are modified by a few factors, and the result looked up on a simple chart. Units which take more than a specific number of casualties become &amp;quot;Shaken&amp;quot;.  Commanders have a limited ability to rally Shaken troops, returning them, at least temporarily, to more or less full effectiveness.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Games are scenario based rather than the familiar points based systems.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The turn sequence is based on a unique card based system which emphasizes command control and battlefield friction.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
